Share with:
Risk Manager Job (Financial Services), Jakarta, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Risk Management
Industry:
Banking & Finance
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Negotiable
Created:
05 May 2014
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of an expanding Financing Holdings Company within the financial service industry in Indonesia. Our respected client is seeking a candidate with management experience for the job of Risk Manager, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. The winning candidate will mainly be responsible for credit analysis across the firm as well as ongoing credit review of an existing portfolio of counterparties to ensure that they are consistent with the Companys’ credit policies and risk appetite.  The winning candidate will report directly to the CFO part of the SME division.
Key job responsibilities include:
Credit analysis and review of a portfolio of credits
Analyze, structure and approve transactions within existing limits
Preparation of credit proposals and reviewing documentation
Providing recommendations and highlighting risk issues to front office and senior approvers
Monitoring market developments to assess credit quality of counterparties
Responsible for the end-to-end credit review and analysis. As part of the team, will perform due diligence of small and medium enterprises and legal documentation to form a view of exposure being proposed that is in line with the companys’ credit policy
Supervise team in all components of ERM and/or risk management methodologies including risk diagnostics, identification, quantification, policies and procedures, monitoring, corporate governance and reporting, and risk systems
Requirements:
Bachelor’s degree in finance or business major from a reputable university
At least 5 years’ experience, with some supervisory experience
Relevant work experience in Risk covering areas such as Credit Risk, Market Risk, Operational Risk or Liquidity Risk. Includes knowledge of the risk tools and processes within a specific risk area including risk diagnostics, policies and procedures, industry best practices;  risk assessment, key driver analysis, risk quantification and modelling
5+ years working in the Financial Services Industry such as in Banking, Capital Market, and/or Insurance
Strong understanding of Risk related Regulatory Requirements, such as Basel II/III, Solvency II, IFRS/IAS, AML/Fraud
Understanding of Lending Value Chain and Operations (both Front & Back Office) within Retail and Commercial Banking
Excellent communication and facilitation skills
Effective team management and leadership skills
Detailed and accurate
Implementing and enhancing internal controls over all aspects of the operations.
Leadership ability and time management skills
Ability to solve practical problems and carry out responsibility under general and little supervision
Able to work under pressure, meet deadline and teamwork.
Availability to work overtime, particularly around the month-end close
Ability to work well under pressure and balance multiple priorities.
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.